{
  "stem": "293.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Pfefferberg.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we just arrived to Cracow.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, we are not in Cracow yet.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You see, in the city of [INAUDIBLE], because I was assistant to the doctor who was the chief operating doctor-- I was participating in all the operations-- not only on the Polish soliders, but also on the German soldiers who was brought to the hospital.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We received a piece of paper signed by the army with a German spread eagle, you know, that we have a right to go outside the hospital to the field to pick up the wounded soldiers.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I kept this.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You see?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When we-- when they decide to move out from city of [INAUDIBLE], the German, and give it to the Russian so the river [INAUDIBLE] became the [INAUDIBLE] line, you know, between Russia and Germany from 1939 until later on, till June 1947-- till 1941.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They took us by train back to Germany.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the train stop in city of Cracow.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we-- they were holding us in the--",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I know the city where, where I was born.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I know the station, every inch of it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They put us in the first class waiting room.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There were a couple hundred of the officers.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we were waiting because they were changing the train to take us to Germany.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Then I noticed a strange fellow staying on the rear door holding a guard, a soldier, not SS man, not Gestapo-- soldier.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I came to him because I spoke very well German, you know, educated language, German, not the slang.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I ask him a simple question.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[BACKROUND NOISE] Can you [GERMAN] So I took the piece of paper what I got it from the authorities in [INAUDIBLE] and show it to him.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Read it.",
      "word_count": 2
    }
  ],
